  "text": "All women underwent a long GnRH agonist stimulation protocol as previously described [CITATION_1] . Women were identi®ed as being at risk of developing OHSS if >20 follicles were noted on ultrasound with a serum E 2 level >13 200 pmol/l. In these women, gonadotrophins were withheld, GnRH agonist continued and administration of hCG was delayed until the serum E 2 level fell to <10 000 pmol/l.",
